        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " so that he reigned not) in Jerusalem “; but the Syriac and Vulg. support the existing Hebrew text. The LXX. begins the verse thus: “And he did the evil before the Lord, according to all that his fathers had done; “and adds, after the clause about the fine, “and the king took him away to Egypt.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Condemned the land in.—Fined the land.—So Kings: “laid a fine upon the land.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Condemned the land in.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Fined the land.—So",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " Kings: “laid a fine upon the land.”",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Riblah was in Syria, on the river Orontes. Necho may have ordered or enticed Jehoahaz to meet him there.",
